parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield gasket can cause the windshield to become loose and potentially detach from the vehicle, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The windshield is not tightly secured by the gasket
the gasket works its way out while operating the vehicle
the gasket comes loose up to several inches on the vertical and horizontal
the windshield glass separates from the weather stripping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause a loss of power to various components, including lights, wipers, and brakes, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loss of power to one or more sides of the vehicle
excessive heat in the switch box
failure of electrical components such as lights
